The Easee One and Hypervolt Home 3 Pro are two of the most premium home EV chargers fighting for the same buyer: someone who wants more than a basic charger, cares about design, and is willing to pay a bit extra for quality. Both sit above the budget tier, both look great on a wall, and both pack features that cheaper chargers simply don't offer.

But they're built on fundamentally different philosophies. The Easee is a Scandinavian design piece with multi-charger flexibility. The Hypervolt is a UK-built all-rounder with the best build quality in the business. Let's find out which one earns your money.

